To send an image or file, clients can enter the "/file" command followed by the file path, e.g., `/file /path/to/image.jpg`. The recipient address will then be requested, and the file will be sent to the specified recipient in binary form, encoded in base64.

Emoji support can be achieved by simply sending Unicode emoji characters in text messages, and they will be displayed correctly on clients with Unicode support. There are no additional changes required in the code to enable the use of emojis in chat messages.

Please note that to transfer larger files or images, the buffer size may need to be increased or the data should be transferred in chunks. However, this may lead to increased complexity and require additional error handling, such as sending acknowledgments for chunks and retransmissions for dropped packets.
